 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search IP Associate Microsoft 7,140 reviews Redmond, WA 98052 Microsoft 7,140 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Partner with Us, Shape the Future.  As an Intellectual Property Associate in Microsoft's U.S. Intellectual Property Group, in its Corporate, External & Legal Affairs department, you'll have a unique opportunity to work alongside a diverse team of professionals who are focused on building and maintaining one of the world’s great intellectual property portfolios. This 2-year fellowship starting August 2021 will expose you to attorneys and engineers who apply their expertise to build Microsoft’s patent portfolio in areas as diverse as artificial intelligence, gaming, virtual reality, productivity, and cloud computing. 
Responsibilities 
The Role.  As an Intellectual Property Associate at Microsoft, you will work within our Intellectual Property Group in Redmond, Washington during your 2-year fellowship. Your responsibilities may include: 
Helping to harvest patentable ideas from engineers 
Reviewing and making recommendations about which ideas to pursue 
Working with our tools to coordinate work on applications, such as tracking filing deadlines and other requirements 
Participating in legal and professional development training 
Conducting research on issues related to innovation and patent law 
Drafting patent applications, patent memos, and other patent-related documents under the supervision of senior attorneys 
Working with senior attorneys to train and counsel engineers on patent matters 
Qualifications 
Must be a current 3rd year student or recent graduate from an ABA accredited law school 
Undergraduate degree, substantive coursework, or working knowledge in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or another STEM-related subject such as Physics or Math that will enable the Associate to be comfortable in a highly technical setting 
Excellent analytical ability and drafting skills 
Excellent oral and written communications skills and the ability to communicate effectively across a diverse group of internal and external stakeholders 
Demonstrated ability to work efficiently, meet deadlines, and manage multiple projects in a fast-paced environment 
Ability to collaborate with others to complete work 
Ability to research and learn new concepts quickly to facilitate problem solving 
Preferred patent bar admission or plan to sit for the Patent Bar Exam 
Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form. 
